Write a script to print the length of each and every string using arrays.
------------------Script--------------------------
#!/bin/bash

arr=("Apple" "Mango" "cherry" "date")
for str in "${arr[@]}"
do
        echo "String: $str, Length: ${#str}"
done
-----------------------output----------------------
String: Apple, Length: 5
String: Mango, Length: 5
String: cherry, Length: 6
String: date, Length: 4
